[I] Python-powered, cross-platform, Unix-gazing shell

[T] Xonsh is a modern, full-featured and cross-platform python shell. The
[T] language is a superset of Python 3.6+ with additional shell primitives that
[T] you are used to from Bash and IPython. It works on all major systems
[T] including Linux, OSX, and Windows. Xonsh is meant for the daily use of
[T] experts and novices.

[U] https://xon.sh

[A] Xonsh Authors
[M] René Rebe <rene@exactco.de>

